The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a problem commonly addressed in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a novel approach based on structured prediction to improve the accuracy of pseudo-labeling, which is a common technique used in unsupervised domain adaptation. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves clustering analysis, which falls under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
